09/11/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski, who leads the ruling VMRO-DPMNE, met with Radmila Sekerinska, the new leader of the opposition Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM), on Wednesday (November 8th). 
They agreed to boost political communication and dialogue. 
They also stressed that the government and the opposition must co-operate in implementing Macedonia's strategic goals and improving the quality of life for all citizens. 
(Dnevnik, Vecer - 09/11/06)
